@node install "Ok, where do I put these files ?"
Installation
============

Firstly, make sure all the files in 's' have the script bit set.
Then copy them somewhere in your command path, I use 'S:', a friend of mine
uses "scripts:"

Then copy the two files in 'c' to somewhere in your command path.

That's it !

@{" colour_shift " link colsh}
@{" screenfool   " link screenfool}
@endnode
@node what "What is runraw ?"
What is runraw ?
================

Well, if you are like me and write a lot of software for BBS's, or like
using BBS style doors off-line without paying for the phone bill, this is
the program for you.

What it does is open up a public screen, and stick a window on it, change
the colours to match a BBS, and run your program.

Translation: Gives you a raw: window with the right colours for BBS doors.
@endnode
@node usage
Usage of program
================

Really, really simple.  Just type

	runraw <program>

where program is the name of a BBS style door you wish to run.
Errrm, thats it.
@endnode
